Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with solving inverse problems efficiently, which involves numerical methods and algorithms. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper may involve visualization of the data and results, as well as graphical representation of the simultaneous source framework. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper may involve developing new algorithms or modifying existing ones to handle non-uniform data variance and missing data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although not directly related, the simultaneous source framework can be applied to network analysis and modeling, which falls under this category. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper may involve image processing and analysis, which is a subfield of computer vision.
